title: Which Kpop idols are half Korean? - Quora

response.answer_text: Somi - Ennik Somi Douma, known by her Korean name Jeon So-mi or mononymously as Somi, is a Korean-Canadian singer based in South Korea, best known for finishing first in Mnet's survival reality program Produce 101 and debuting in former South Korean girl group I.O.I. She has debuted solo and released her latest mv called ‘Birthday’. Source: Wikipedia   2) Vernon Vernon, born Han-solVernon Choi, is one of the 13 boys of the popular K-Pop group SEVENTEEN. Born in New York to an American mother and a Korean father, Vernon moved to Seoul when he was five and grew up there. Source: Wikipedia    3) Shannon Williams Shannon Areum Williams Lees, known professionally as Shannon, is a British-South Korean singer and actress based in South Korea. She officially debuted as a solo artist in December 2014 with her digital single, Daybreak Rain. Shannon has announced that she is leaving her agency (MBK ent) and Korea to focus more on composing new songs in the near future. Source: Wikipedia    4) Huening kai Huening Kai is a Korean-American singer under Big Hit Entertainment. He is a member of the boy group TXT. His mother is known to be Korean while his father is American (but of German descent). Source: Wikipedia    5) Insooni Kim In-soon, better known by her stage name, Insooni, is a South Korean singer who made her debut in 1978 as a member of Hee Sisters. She is the daughter of a Korean woman and an American GI who was formerly stationed in Korea. She has recorded a total of 19 albums, 14 of them full-length albums. She is acclaimed as South Korea's R&B diva, having garnered a wide range of fans over her 41+ year career. Source: Wikipedia   5) Michelle Lee Michelle Lee was born September 9, 1991, in Paju, South Korea, to a Korean mother and African American father. is a South Korean singer. After successfully auditioning for K-pop Star Season 1 in 2011, she was eventually signed to YG Entertainment as part of a new girl group called SuPearls. However, after two years of training, the group was suddenly disbanded before they could debut and Lee's contract was nullified. She then went on to two other agencies and eventually had released album's. She is currently a singer and a rapper. Source: Wikipedia    6) Kangnam Yasuo Namekawa, better known by his stage name Kangnam, is a Korean–Japanese singer and television personality. He was the vocalist and oldest member of the South Korean hip-hop group, M.I.B. He made his recording debut in South Korea with the single, "Say My Name," just before his debut as a member of M.I.B. Source: Wikipedia    7) Kim Samuel Samuel Kim Arredondo, better known by his stage name Samuel, is an American-born South Korean singer who was a part of the short-lived hip hop duo 1Punch in 2015. In April 2017, he participated in the reality television series Produce 101 Season 2 during the first half of 2017. Source: Wikipedia    I'm pretty sure there's many more half korean kpop idols but for now the above are the most popular half korean artists who are known widely in Korea and abroad.
